.TH MDE 1 "2026-05-19" "MDE 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mde \- Mackes Desktop Environment primary CLI entry point
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mde
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
[\fISUBCOMMAND\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mde
is the user-facing CLI for the Mackes Desktop Environment (MDE).
It launches the Workbench, runs the first-run wizard, surfaces
deep-link "focus" routes (\fB\-\-focus\fR), and exposes the
\fBupdate\fR / \fBabout\fR / \fBdrawer\fR subcommands.
.P
On the v1.x → v2.0.0 transition release, this binary is a thin
shim that execs the legacy \fB/usr/bin/mackes\fR script with the
same argv. The v2.0.0 cut moves the Python entry point under
\fImde/\fR and this shim becomes a no-op exec.
.SH OPTIONS
See
.B mackes(1)
for the full option list during the v1.x compatibility window.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MDE_HOME
Override the default MDE state directory.
.B MACKES_HOME
is honored as a one-release fallback (deprecated; removed in v2.1).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/mde/panel.toml
Panel configuration (v2.0.0).
.TP
.I ~/.config/mackes-shell/
Legacy v1.x configuration; auto-migrated to
.I ~/.config/mde/
by
.B mde-migrate-from-1x(1)
on first login.
.SH SEE ALSO
.B mde-session(1),
.B mde-panel(1),
.B mded(8),
.B mde-migrate-from-1x(1),
.B mde-shell-migrate-v2(1)
